\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\cvar_{t}+f\left(\cvar\right)_{x}=0\label{eq:cons-smooth}
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We also assume the system is hyperbolic, which implies that 
\begin_inset Formula $f_{x}$
\end_inset

 has real values everywhere.
 Since we are considering a scalar system, this is automatically satisfied.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For a particular initial condition 
\begin_inset Formula $\cvar_{0}:\mathbb{R}\rightarrow\mathbb{R}$
